: \(X_t=(X_{t,1},X_{t,2}),t = 1,...,N\) \[X_{t,1}= aX_{t,2}+\epsilon_t\] \((1,-\tilde a)\),

\(X_t=(X_{t,1},X_{t,2}),t = 1,...,N\) \[X_t=\Pi_1X_{t-1}+\Pi_2X_{t-2}+\mu+\epsilon_t\] \(\Pi_1\) \[\Pi_{1,1}^{(1)} = 0.924,\Pi_{2,1}^{(1)} = -0.134\] \[\Pi_{2,1}^{(1)} = 0.001,\Pi_{2,2}^{(1)} = 0.986\], \(\Pi_2\) \[\Pi_{1,1}^{(2)}= 0.047,\Pi_{2,1}^{(2)}= 0.403\] \[\Pi_{2,1}^{(2)}= 0.002,\Pi_{2,2}^{(2)}= -0.044\]

\(\mu\) \[\mu=(0.073,-0.004)\], \[\epsilon_t=(\epsilon_{t,1},\epsilon_{t,2})\] \[E[\epsilon_{t,i}]= 0,D[\epsilon_{t,i}] = 20\], \[cov(\epsilon_{t,1},\epsilon_{t,2}= 0)\]
